result.execSummary:
On one or more charges, the deferred prosecution or sentencing agreement(s) on this case were fulfilled, and the charge(s) were dismissed.

The defendant David G Schaefer was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. David G Schaefer is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • David G Schaefer was found guilty of Possess Methamphetamine Precursors, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.65.
  • David G Schaefer was found guilty of Possession of Methamphetamine, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(g).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant David G Schaefer in court with attorney Erik C. Johnson.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

  Court questions defendant regarding plea. Advises of Constitutional Rights and elements of the charge.  Court finds plea made freely, voluntarily & Intelligently.  Court relies on the criminal complaint for a factual basis. 

 BY THE COURT:  Court finds a sufficient factual basis to support the charges.  Court accepts defendant's plea and finds defendant guilty of Counts 2 & 4.
Court accepts defendant's plea; approves and signs the 24 month DPA on Ct. 1.

Atty Hendee makes sentencing recommendations.
Atty Johnson makes sentencing arguments.
Defendant makes a statement to the court.
